      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "EVENTUATE (7) charged out of the boxes with a strong early split and went straight to the front, scoring an all the way win (34.41) over 600m at this track. Recorded the quickest time on the card last start. Can make it two on the bounce. BAREFOOT ZULU (8) was well fancied last time on the strength of a win two back but could only manage sixth (25.82) at Murray Bridge. Strong form has emerged from his last run. Has the ability to give this a shake. BAILIESTON (4) scored over 525m at this track last time when leading throughout to claim a Grade 4/5 (29.96) latest. Likely to enjoy the staying trip for the first time. Boasts a strong record from this draw with five wins and two minor placings from eight starts. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. DARK MIRACLE (1) was a surprise last-start placegetter worth considering.",
